With the default httpchk, glance-api always show warning in the logs
"WARNING glance.api.middleware.version_negotiation [..] Unknown version.
Returning version choices", with the /versions added, there is no
warning in the log.

Change-Id: I086cb23c30b9e3ddc5eac68cba42d03ed907138c
'}]
commit_message:
Add "httpchk /versions" for glance-api haproxy.

With the default httpchk, glance-api always show warning in the logs
"WARNING glance.api.middleware.version_negotiation [..] Unknown version.
Returning version choices", with the /versions added, there is no
warning in the log.

Change-Id: I086cb23c30b9e3ddc5eac68cba42d03ed907138c

commit_message:
[Verify] Fixing issue with SSL deployments

Now options 'disable_ssl_certificate_validation' and 'ca_certificates_file'
are configured in the Tempest config file and values for these options are
taken from credentials that user specified.

Config options https_insecure and https_cacert were removed since they were
marked as "deprecated_for_removal".

Change-Id: I74083bc9af21969dd836f852712b81abd3ec74dc

commit_message:
[Ci] Check Heat service availability in tests.ci.osresources

Make a check if `heat' service is available
in tests.ci.osresources to prevent failures while quering heat
resources on jobs that does not have heat installed.

This fixes issues with job gate-rally-dsvm-manila-multibackend

Change-Id: Id3c4c24114d6db99e9e4fce43162fa6ce0b20d61
Closes-Bug: #1518913

Marking as work-in-progress because I want to have another try at getting WSME to do the validation. Currently, if I just delete the mandatory_attr method in JsonPatchType, the following happens:

1. tests that remove mandatory attributes fail with a server error, because a Port or Node object is created, then replaced with a MagicMock (which doesn't know about the uuid), then when the MagicMock is asked for its uuid it causes an error. Currently we don't hit that problem because the object is never constructed in the first place.
2. If I manually fix up the MagicMock's uuid and run the test to completion, the deletion goes ahead and no error is raised.

So I'd like, at a minimum, to fix up the mocking."}, {'account_id': 3, 'date': '2015-10-29 14:45:00.000000000', 'content': 'Patch Set 3: Verified-1

commit_message:
Get mandatory patch attrs from WSME properties

Attributes which are mandatory (ie, required for object creation) should
not be removable. However, some attributes (such as Node.chassis_uuid)
are not required for object creation, but should not be removable if
they are set. This commit does the following:

 - rename JsonPatchType.mandatory_attrs to non_removable_attrs to better
   describe its meaning,
 - change its return type to set-of-strings for faster lookup
 - ensure all mandatory attributes on the type being patched are
   included in the set of non-removable attributes,
 - add a new field, JsonPatchType._extra_non_removable_attrs, which
   should be a set of attributes that are not required for creation but
   should not be removed if set.

Since the object to be patched does not exist at patch-validation time,
we leave the validation logic in methods of JsonPatchType and
subclasses. This means introspecting the types to be patched.

Closes-Bug: #1284781

Change-Id: I2bb7fed2c776c8d63535c5ee19cdc218e57806e3

commit_message:
Fix mistypes and minor code style issues
1. Fix mistypes, except interfaces
2. Fix old style classes (now inherit from object)
3. Fix single quoted docstrings
4. Redundant parenthesis
5. shadow builtins in locals (aka str or type as variable names)

Change-Id: Ie7c746c6e603472452766ba96cd94a6a3b232d6c
Closes-bug: #1517507

commit_message:
VMware: enable two more values in validators for gw devices

This patch simply ensures the network gateway API extension accepts
value with an underscore for ipsec transport types.
Unfortunately this module was not moved to openstack/vmware-nsx
during decomposition and therefore this patch is being proposed on
the neutron repository.

Change-Id: I5e8532ea73dac286bab1c7e39a7e0b33681e2d7e
Partial-Bug: #1474834

[autohelp] Add table label for RST reference

Each table need to be markuped up for reference.
In case the label is set at outside of inclusion,
Sphinx can not properly treat the label.

Change-Id: I2257471300ca5752ba717858a14d4fa26f62916f

commit_message:
Add constraints and timeouts from file in single step

To avoid pcmk reconfiguring the resources on each config change,
we want to apply the constraints and timeouts from file.

We also *do not* want to alter the timeouts for a few ocf resources
which are rabbitmq, neutron-netns-cleanup and neutron-ovs-cleanup

Change-Id: I6875f19e1f34f0fdcf0928421f49b61d857ca7c8
Co-Authored-By: Andrew Beekhof <abeekhof@redhat.com>

revisions:
[{'created': '2015-11-03 16:12:45.000000000', 'message': 'Remove `local` flag

For now `shotgun` always executes on the `mcollective` docker
container. `local` flag was created to be able to execute a command on
`localhost` which, in the past, was master node. But for now it is
`mcollective` and as the result we get diagnostic snapshots from
`mcollective`. There is no any reason to have `local` flag for execution
a command on the `localhost` (it will be always `mcollective`
container). If we need to get diagnostic snapshots for some particular
container we can create command for such purpose. For example:

DUMP:
  dump:
    master:
      objects:
        - type: command
          command: `dockerctl shell mcollective rpm -qa`
          to_file: mcollective_installed_rpms.txt

Change-Id: Iac1d9ea37400e4d202a9bc673c5fa3d3d185701b
Partial-Bug: #1511730
'}, {'created': '2015-11-10 17:34:11.000000000', 'message': 'Replace `local` with `remote` flag

Execute a command on local host by default. Execute a command on the
remote host only if it was specifically requested.

Change-Id: Iac1d9ea37400e4d202a9bc673c5fa3d3d185701b
Partial-Bug: #1511730

commit_message:
Fix argument order for assertEqual to (expected, observed)

assertEqual expects that the arguments provided to it should be
(expected, observed).If a particluar order is kept as a convention,
then it helps to provide a cleaner message to the developer if Unit Tests
fail. There are several Unit Test files where the arguments for assertEqual
have been swapped. This commit fixes the issue in networking-midonet.

Change-Id: I00daee7e5628151e38d8becdfa7057c78aa48abe
Closes-Bug: #1259292
(cherry picked from commit c3bcfd3dd5b3482df9a018d7a668d9f8232b0175)

commit_message:
Import pep3134daemon as local module

pep3134daemon is now imported from local path
rather than pip. This generated many issues
as the package is not in the global-requirements.txt
of kilo and liberty. Also pbr in the kilo release
does not support env markers which further complitated
the installation. This change needs to be backported to
stable/kilo also.

Also some minor fix for RST format.

Change-Id: I34db28ffc928703b01e6430a661214d66d81c519

commit_message:
Added logging for haproxy to rsyslog

The change adds logging for haproxy on localhost through the use
of rsyslog which is now a dependency. The logs will be stored in
/var/log/haproxy which will later be indexed and shipped to the
logging server. The change makes it possible to debug issues with
haproxy using specific log files instead of having to go digging
through syslog.

Change-Id: Id942ce159ea45703259f7aff0e5a85780a83370b
Signed-off-by: Kevin Carter <kevin.carter@rackspace.com>
(cherry picked from commit 08a0f535503c9d709b2d9375a7f17f9841d01d0d)

subject: Kilo backport
revisions:
[{'created': '2015-11-23 12:17:55.000000000', 'message': 'Kilo backport

Service_provider in neutron.conf
	In kilo it is not possible to add service
	provider config. Thats why the configuration has
	to be set in neutron.conf

Add namespace to extension
	In kilo an extension for neutron still
	needs a get_namespace method.

Hack around neutrons fixed plugin rules
	The list of allowed services is fixed in kilo.
	This commit adds BGPVPN to the allowed services.

Align unittests to kilo
	bgpvpn_id is given in kwargs not in args.

Change-Id: I3b5fa02af73c6111d38a7e99f372e25e2e469510
'}]
commit_message:
Kilo backport

Service_provider in neutron.conf
	In kilo it is not possible to add service
	provider config. Thats why the configuration has
	to be set in neutron.conf

Add namespace to extension
	In kilo an extension for neutron still
	needs a get_namespace method.

Hack around neutrons fixed plugin rules
	The list of allowed services is fixed in kilo.
	This commit adds BGPVPN to the allowed services.

Align unittests to kilo
	bgpvpn_id is given in kwargs not in args.

Change-Id: I3b5fa02af73c6111d38a7e99f372e25e2e469510

[{'created': '2015-11-17 23:08:47.000000000', 'message': 'Reset stack status even when lock engine_id is None

Having a stack which is wedged UPDATE_IN_PROGRESS due to another bug,
restarting heat-engine should have resulted in the stack being reset to
UPDATE_FAILED. However the reset was skipped because the lock engine_id
was None.

This change removes the engine_id check since it is possible in practice
for an UPDATE_IN_PROGRESS stack to not be locked.

Since it is possible for the stack to change state in the unlocked
window, a check is added that the stack is still IN_PROGRESS before the
reset is performed.

Change-Id: I1739ccbdf75af35aac5be16b99200975df58b8e2
Closes-Bug: #1514615
(cherry picked from commit 44b2f0965dd329cf45a151705b0648819acff8c7)
'}]
commit_message:
Reset stack status even when lock engine_id is None

Having a stack which is wedged UPDATE_IN_PROGRESS due to another bug,
restarting heat-engine should have resulted in the stack being reset to
UPDATE_FAILED. However the reset was skipped because the lock engine_id
was None.

This change removes the engine_id check since it is possible in practice
for an UPDATE_IN_PROGRESS stack to not be locked.

Since it is possible for the stack to change state in the unlocked
window, a check is added that the stack is still IN_PROGRESS before the
reset is performed.

Change-Id: I1739ccbdf75af35aac5be16b99200975df58b8e2
Closes-Bug: #1514615

commit_message:
Expose quiesce unquiesce API

Currently the Nova provides single VM snapshot API (createImage), which will
take a consistency snapshot of a VM and regarding volumes, and will quiesce
unquiesce VM automatily with guest agent support.This method is good
for single VM consistency snapshot, but no way to make consistency
snapshot for an application which consists of multiple VMs.

Provide quiesce unquiesce API from Nova, to make consistency snapshot
of an application, which consists of a  group of VMs, for disaster
recovery purpose from another site.

Atomic quiesce / unquiesce API will allow to make snapshot of a group of VMs
in a transaction way, for example, quiesce VM1, quiesce VM2, quiesce VM3,
snapshot VM1's volumes, snapshot VM2's volumes, snapshot VM3's volumes,
unquiesce VM3, unquiesce VM2, unquiesce VM1. For some telecom application,
the order is important for a group of VMs with strong relationship.

APIImpact: Expose quiesce unquiesce API
DocImpact: Expose quiesce unquiesce API

Blueprint:
https://blueprints.launchpad.net/nova/+spec/expose-quiesce-unquiesce-api

Change-Id: I3cc247fba7a07dceb42704022444a450c31ea0e8
Signed-off-by: Chaoyi Huang <joehuang@huawei.com>

commit_message:
Document an EOL and release dates

There are various discussions about the fact that Juno is EOL in
November, but there is no hard documented date when such a thing is
expected to happen. Document when Juno was released and when it will EOL
- as well as the same for kilo, liberty and mitaka.

Change-Id: Iada72d966e93b8ff1f0febb4473a92fdd0532e51

commit_message:
Copy the env to the backup stack in failed update

When an update fails, we currently update the environment of the stack
to contain both the new and old parameters and types. Unfortunately we
don't do that for the backup stack which is reused. This patch adds the
environment change.

Change-Id: I4dc5dd35e4aeee498dd8960a1000913e97b924d5
Closes-Bug: 1508096
(cherry picked from commit 88da460316e2c18b3ceb58f51dcf0bda717a18a3
                       and 13c68910704844719b2d3de353d2db276377bf11)

commit_message:
virtual function stubs patch fixes

1. The remove function interface for port did not match actual code
2. remove switch should provide the object in the interface and
delete it from the local db after dispatch
3. Make sure we allocate local network id before calling dispatch

Change-Id: Ie37f1eaea378316ab5df2d3ee273335a4e269ae8

Add a 'bandit' target to tox.ini

All checkers are enabled, and we only need to silence one silence false
positive.

Change-Id: I829f2b2ef7e94b76b348c1e6ec6e4249009724c8

It seems here that a new extension loader is being introduced. In order to make sure the UX is consistent across plugins, I would rather see this implemented as an improvement to the core neutron extension management code.'}, {'account_id': 1561, 'date': '2015-06-08 13:15:35.000000000', 'content': "Patch Set 9:

First off, I realize this isn't the first case of vendor specific REST API additions.  However, I'm fundamentally opposed to them.  I think allowing any sort of vendor specific support through the API is harmful to the Neutron mission of providing a useful abstraction.  The more of this stuff there is, the less useful Neutron is."}, {'account_id': 261, 'date': '2015-06-09 18:45:02.000000000', 'content': "Patch Set 9: Code-Review-1

On a personal note I agree with Russell. Vendor extensions are bad for the project. On the other hand I work for a vendor, and I've developed some. So I kind of understand where the need for having such extensions come from. In the microversioning proposal I am advocating for keeping vendor extensions, with the caveat that they would not be able to alter existing neutron resources, and will never be documented or versioned as neutron APIs.

For this particular patch, you are enabling some neutron extensions which exist on contrail's neutron endpoint (I think for those neutron would just act as a proxy like any other open contrail API).
The problem I see here is that you're not providing your user a way to discover these extensions, apparently. Will they appear if a user does a GET on v2.0/extensions?

On another unrelated note, I wonder why you keep this plugin. It seems all you need neutron for is quota enforcement (which is broken by the way), authZ, and Keystone integration. IMHO it would be a lot simpler for you to provide these features on the OpenContrail mgmt layer."}, {'account_id': 3, 'date': '2015-10-01 19:11:08.000000000', 'content': 'Patch Set 9: Verified-1

Removing initialization of clients that are not used

Removing initialization of some clients from BaseIdentityV3Test class
because they are not used anywhere.

commit_message:
Retry certain DB transactions on DBConnectionError

This patch extends the existing _retry_on_deadlock function to also
retry certain database transactions when a connection error occurs
(oslo.db.exception.DBConnectionError). This has the benefit of providing
some tolerance for database restarts.

Change-Id: Ia2a658a2e7bc050553539122bbc01d5784d8dc92

Think that this is a good place to start improving on our race conditions.

Although, this fix does not apply to all the cases like someone doing large number of concurrent updates at the same time where many queries would result into same updated_at value at the return of _image_get and at query.update(..) to run into this race condition.

However, from a general use perspective and for most of the calls, this MP lgtm.

Would like another opinion for +2/+A.

Thanks for taking care of this!'}, {'account_id': 3, 'date': '2014-09-20 01:36:46.000000000', 'content': 'Patch Set 1: Verified-1

It will not work for several reasons.
First, updated_at is not added to values in _format_image_to_db() in db/__init__.py. So previous_timestamp is always None in db/sqlalchemy/api.py. For that reason 
query = query.filter_by(updated_at=previous_timestamp)
does not make sense.
Second, even if we can get _format_image_to_db() to pass updated_at value, it would be truncated to seconds (but we expect millis), due to the way of storage in the database. It means that even after our filter by timestamp another process can easily update values.'}, {'account_id': 8127, 'date': '2014-09-22 17:37:20.000000000', 'content': 'Uploaded patch set 2.'}, {'account_id': 8127, 'date': '2014-09-22 17:39:18.000000000', 'content': 'Uploaded patch set 3.'}, {'account_id': 8127, 'date': '2014-09-22 17:42:31.000000000', 'content': "Patch Set 3:

Mike, thanks, really nice catch about the updated_at not being serialized. Fixed that.

Speaking about milliseconds precision - this may be try for some database, and that's why the current solution is not ideal. However it will solve at least part of the problem, while the better solution may be to have a dedicated millisecond-precision column for timestamp and/or keep track of the changed properties instead of updating all of them"}, {'account_id': 3, 'date': '2014-09-22 19:30:46.000000000', 'content': 'Patch Set 3: Verified-1

While I think the code looks good, this seems to be re-inventing a feature that's built in to Sqlalchemy. Did you look into the 'version_id_col' feature when working on this? Admittedly it doesn't seem to be very well documented, but it provides optimistic locking in a similar way. On the code side, I believe it just requires a mapping added to the db model of the object you want locking for. On the downside we would need to add a uuid column to the db and populate it for the version_id, so a migration would be required."}, {'account_id': 8127, 'date': '2014-10-24 09:54:17.000000000', 'content': 'Patch Set 8:

Eddie, that's right: when I was considering different options for fixing this issue (see [1]) one of the options was to introduce a dedicated version column, which will not have precision problems - and reusing the existing functionality is definitely one of the options.
However, this patch was initially supposed to be a quick fix introduced at the end of iteration, so I wanted to minimise the need of migrations and model changes before the release.

The change didn't land in Juno unfortunately,  but the bug is still tagged as "juno-backport-potential", so we will probably want to backport it to stable/juno at some point. So I would prefer not to introduce changes which may require migrations


[1] http://lists.openstack.org/pipermail/openstack-dev/2014-September/047158.html'}, {'account_id': 5347, 'date': '2014-11-05 18:44:27.000000000', 'content': "Patch Set 8: Code-Review+1

commit_message:
Fixes a race during v2 concurrent image update

Introduces an optimistic lock when updating images in database:
if another request has modified the previously fetched image
the update query will fail (as it is filtered by exact match of last timestamp),
which wil raise a Conflict exception

Change-Id: I1387137a980aa7d7b81a64376c46ba430830630a
Closes-Bug: #1371728
Partial-Bug: #1372564

commit_message:
Drop eventlet getsockopt workaround

Workaround for eventlet getsockopt has been added in
I187b69f75b8bcfe16facd41e69b1cd0490dae605 with explicit statement that
it should be dropped after eventlet fix it on their side. The fix has
been already merged
https://bitbucket.org/eventlet/eventlet/commits/609f230 so we are free
to drop our workaround for this one.

Change-Id: I3da4a0430e7e9ce1191ef0f3f67adb295d450a24

commit_message:
Check updated properties are actually updated in V2

When an image is being updated, V2 doesn't check if a parameter
is actually being updated. It would be good to catch this
before the client sends it to the server.

Change-Id: Ibf348d2e04494fa3e7802758add1fd740d62f2a1
Fixes-bug: #1307412

    reviewing code. The more you participate in the community the more
    rewarding it is for you. You may also notice that the more you get to know
    people and get to be known, the faster your patches will be reviewed and
    eventually approved. Get to know others and become known by doing code

commit_message:
Replace tearDown with addCleanup in unit tests

Infra team has indicated that tearDown should not be used, and should
be replaced with addCleanup in all places. This patch removes the
few cases of tearDown in Glance.

Change-Id: I8f8ff3ed653a44893b50ccb2f89bdb3a3809216a

While I agree with Christopher that documentation *in general* should use example.com per 2606, I think we should perhaps provide a different way of documenting this. For example, we could do:

    http://<swift-host>[:<swift-port>]/path/to/object

Because it would provide the user some context, in otherwords, "I'm specifying this as a --location, so it won't be looked up in the service catalog. I have to provide a lot more information to Glance in order for it to understand the URL.

With that nit taken care of, I'm +2 on this.'}, {'account_id': 18791, 'date': '2015-10-16 08:01:59.000000000', 'content': 'Patch Set 6: Code-Review-1

Maybe create a single rule for this and make it default?'}, {'account_id': 5202, 'date': '2014-12-03 18:09:12.000000000', 'content': 'Patch Set 7: Code-Review-2

I think this change needs more discussion before moved forward:

1) The blueprint linked should have spec written for it. The blueprint description gives different end goal for this change than the related keystone spec ( https://review.openstack.org/#/c/135408/ ).
2) We should not use policies in our examples that are not explained in doc/source/policies.rst. The lack of the documentation gives direct signal to our deployers that they need to go and read the code to understand example, which defeats the purpose of example. This was flagged first time at PS 4.
3) If this change is meant to be cross project implementation of new default roles, this needs to be discussed with wider audience, not just hoping that any of the projects merges it and then using that to get the rest agreeing.

Good next steps:
1) Start the discussion on the dev mailing list what are you actually trying to reach with these changes, how you want to do it and collect feedback.
2) Bring your case to Cross Project and individual project weekly meetings after the wide consensus has been reached. https://wiki.openstack.org/wiki/Meetings has details of the meetings and their agendas.

Understanding the scale I think this needs to be planned and executed carefully if at all. Thanks for working on this and please understand this is not you. We just need to take step back and approach this right to avoid any cross project conflicts this scale of change might bring.'}, {'account_id': 12000, 'date': '2015-06-03 18:32:22.000000000', 'content': "Patch Set 7: Code-Review-1

Hey Andre!

Cheers,
Ian"}, {'account_id': 2218, 'date': '2015-06-03 18:58:01.000000000', 'content': "Patch Set 7:

commit_message:
Creating a policy sample

Creating a policy sample containing cloud_admin,
project_admin and project_member roles.

Related commit:
Cinder   - https://review.openstack.org/#/c/123433/
Nova     - https://review.openstack.org/#/c/123428/
Neutron  - https://review.openstack.org/#/c/123440/
Keystone - https://review.openstack.org/#/c/123509/

DocImpact

blueprint policy-sample

Co-Authored-By: Thiago Paiva Brito <thiagop@lsd.ufcg.edu.br>

closes-bug: #1391504
Change-Id: I56ba10bac0c6eec3effde0156fd07528c8737c97

commit_message:
Make path for db_export_metadefs required

Currently if you call glance-manage db_export_metadefs without
any additional options, it will export all current metadefs
into the glance conf dir (e.g. /etc/glance/metadefs/) without
any warning. If the files already exist it will overwrite them.
Fix make glance-manage db_export_metadefs to require path
for destination folder to hold metadefs.
glance-manage db_export_metadefs /tmp

Change-Id: I561be5a205c2909b7bf80e2e3d10fa3c39f98cba
Closes-Bug: 1367011
DocImpact
Co-Authored-By: Pawel Koniszewski <pawel.koniszewski@intel.com>

commit_message:
Deprecate [paste_deploy]/flavor for auth_strategy

All other projects have switched from using flavor to auth_strategy,
this will bring glance's config files into compliance with other
openstack projects making it easier for deployers to understand what
they're configuring.

DocImpact
UpgradeImpact
Closes-bug: 1406582

commit_message:
Integrity check for images with checksum = "None"

Images on "External sources" have checksum = "None" in the glance db.
These images could be uploaded for example with:
glance image-create --name test-image
               --location=http://some.location.com/image.raw ...

Trying to start an instance with "boot from image (creates volume)"
fails with "Checksum was xxxxxx expected None"

This change will fix this error.

Closes-Bug: 1434040
Change-Id: I9871ee42b1b4572b7e5de9fc912d96ae6996b875

[{'created': '2015-04-06 06:46:57.000000000', 'message': 'force option now acts as boolean, just like can-share

There was some inconsistency in glanceclient options, some boolean
flags were used as boolean while some others required {True,False}.
Now these options can be used like boolean flags, for example

commit_message:
force option now acts as boolean, just like can-share

There was some inconsistency in glanceclient options, some boolean
flags were used as boolean while some others required {True,False}.
Now these options can be used like boolean flags, for example
--is-public and --is-public {True,False} both are allowed. We, after
comming to a common solution, can depricate one method if required(i
prefer to depricate {True,False} method).

Closes-Bug: #1221769
Change-Id: I146e06bf0554ff9184859f3e283629cb5e5c51db

commit_message:
glance v2 image-list now has human-readable option

size of glance images is stored in bytes, but when images are
listed size is displayed in bytes, and it is in not easy for users to
convert size in human understandable format, so added human-readable
option to glance image-list

Change-Id: I85424780b2afe346b218b87949093c157e485371
Closes-Bug: #1433430

Enable status filter for v2

Add a new parameter for image list v2, so that user can
list images which in specific status, such as deleted,
killed, etc.

Closes-Bug: #1432701

commit_message:
Fix HTTP 500 on NotAuthenticated in registry (v1)

If for some reason (absent\invalid token) authentication failed during a
registry call, InternalServerError appeared as long as
exception.NotAuthenticated was not being caught in ImagesController.

This patch fixes the issue by catching the exception and raising
401 Unauthorized.

Change-Id: I38554d166d0d5d16849dbcf7d94158a65d20717d
Closes-Bug: #1450041

commit_message:
Versioned object for Image and ImageMember model

Implementation of oslo.versionedobjects.
This commit consists basic mechanism and first objects - Image and
ImageMember. This should be base of implementation versioning to other
objects.

Partially Implements: blueprint versioned-objects

Change-Id: Id1de23979ee3bf391c1a65fc9845f5bd1d4fbb21

  708  . accrc/invisible_to_admin/demo

  716  #switch back to admin

  721  glance image-list
  722  #opps forgot switching
  723  . accrc/invisible_to_admin/demo

commit_message:
Use oslo.versionedobjects to define artifact types

This patch adds a set of classes which inherit
oslo_versionedobjects.fields.Field type and provide plugin developer
with an ability to define the structure of artifacts using
oslo.versionedobjects as an laternative to the existing "declarative
framework" defined at glance.common.artifacts.definitions.

This is the first patch of the series: for complete support of
oslo.versionedobjects appropriate changes have to be introduced in
plugin loader, object serializer, domain layers etc.

Work-in-progress, but reviews are most appreciated.

Depends-on: I17328209b0b5334c24c893828e04ef19c7354148

Change-Id: I82b500ac6a5fde6a60054a804146dc6ee9dc2a8f

keeping existing --tenant-id option deprecated.

DocImpact

The code is fine. However, this is a thoroughly backwards incompatible change and the change was never prioritized or triaged on Launchpad. I'm personally of the opinion that the bug is invalid."}, {'account_id': 12869, 'date': '2015-02-26 10:32:17.000000000', 'content': 'Patch Set 1:

As per the Glance api reference name should be positional argument. So, the bug is valid in that case.'}, {'account_id': 455, 'date': '2015-02-26 14:33:56.000000000', 'content': "Patch Set 1: Code-Review-1

I get that having no name may not be that intuitive, but doesn't this have the potential to break existing v1 scripts (which have worked for a long time)?"}, {'account_id': 12869, 'date': '2015-02-27 07:12:17.000000000', 'content': 'Patch Set 1:

Hi Stuart
I agreed that this may break existing v1 script. But As per the Glance API reference, name should be placed as a positional argument and we need to modify the existent functionality.
Moreover, while creating an image it will be created with the name of "None" which is not a good option, which will produce the conflict issue while deleting the image.'}, {'account_id': 14501, 'date': '2015-02-27 07:51:08.000000000', 'content': 'Patch Set 1:

I agree with Amandeep'}, {'account_id': 5314, 'date': '2015-02-27 16:02:16.000000000', 'content': 'Patch Set 1: Code-Review-1

We should change the API ref, then.  We do not want to introduce a breaking change into v1.

The name of an image is not required to be unique, so I don't see a customer having 50 images named "None" as different from having 50 images named "Web Server".  Each image has a UUID, so there is definitely a way to tell them apart.  Further, the images can be renamed.

So while I agree that this is an annoyance, and I commend you for noticing and wanting to correct it, I don't think we should make this change.'}, {'account_id': 3, 'date': '2015-04-28 16:34:51.000000000', 'content': 'Patch Set 1: Verified-1

commit_message:
updated the image-create parameter details

Initially, glance image-create works successfully
with no parameters and a image is created with a
name None.

With this patch name parameter is changed to
positional argument.

[{'created': '2015-07-31 11:44:34.000000000', 'message': "Request-id is not getting returned if glance throws 500 error.

Added 'request_id' and 'catch_errors' middleware from oslo_middleware
to return request-id from response. 'catch_errors' is added to catch
all exceptions from application and 'request_id' is used to add
request-id for each API response.

Only 'catch_errors' middleware is added for glance-registry because
here we need to use same request-id generated in glance-api.
If we add 'request_id' middleware to glance-registry then it will
generate new request-id.

Removed BaseContextMiddleware class because now request_id
middleware will add 'request-id' to response headers.

Also this patch fixes below issue:
1. Request ID has a double 'req-' at the start
2. User can send invalid (long string) as request-id to glance
   service using 'X-Openstack-Request-Id' header field.

DocImpact:
1. Added new WSGI middlewares 'request_id' and 'catch_errors' to
   glance-api-paste.ini file.
2. Added new WSGI middleware 'catch_errors' to
   glance-registry-paste.ini file.
3. Do not add 'request_id' middleware to glance-registry-paste.ini,
   otherwise it will generate new request-id for glance-registry
   and will not use request-id passed from glance-api.

Closes-Bug: #1480196
Closes-Bug: #1480191
Closes-Bug: #1478690

Change-Id: Iedd17a9981a4089b4d875dad87c6d5a07a368c24
"}]
commit_message:
Request-id is not getting returned if glance throws 500 error.

Added 'request_id' and 'catch_errors' middleware from oslo_middleware
to return request-id from response. 'catch_errors' is added to catch
all exceptions from application and 'request_id' is used to add
request-id for each API response.

Only 'catch_errors' middleware is added for glance-registry because
here we need to use same request-id generated in glance-api.
If we add 'request_id' middleware to glance-registry then it will
generate new request-id.

Removed BaseContextMiddleware class because now request_id
middleware will add 'request-id' to response headers.

Also this patch fixes below issue:
1. Request ID has a double 'req-' at the start
2. User can send invalid (long string) as request-id to glance
   service using 'X-Openstack-Request-Id' header field.

DocImpact:
1. Added new WSGI middlewares 'request_id' and 'catch_errors' to
   glance-api-paste.ini file.
2. Added new WSGI middleware 'catch_errors' to
   glance-registry-paste.ini file.
3. Do not add 'request_id' middleware to glance-registry-paste.ini,
   otherwise it will generate new request-id for glance-registry
   and will not use request-id passed from glance-api.

Closes-Bug: #1480196
Closes-Bug: #1480191
Closes-Bug: #1478690

Change-Id: Iedd17a9981a4089b4d875dad87c6d5a07a368c24

commit_message:
Parallelizes deleting image segments

When an image is deleted, all its segments are deleted in a serial
fashion. This may lead to slower image deletes especially for images
with a lot of segments. This is a natural target for parallelization
to gain performance on image delete requests.

Change-Id: Ifb7bc54ee10b0999b5a4c7d4f97a618e36342b29

commit_message:
Add option to wait between swift retries

This adds two new options:

    swift_store_retry_get_wait = 1
    swift_store_retry_get_exponential_wait = True

These complement the existing option, swift_store_retry_get_count. If
swift_store_retry_get_wait is not 0, glance will delay by the number of
milliseconds that option specifies between each retry.

If swift_store_retry_get_exponential_wait is set to True, those wait
times are doubled at each successive retry.

DocImpact

Implements: blueprint swift-retry-wait

Change-Id: I575eb501153615e262aaa13202797d25458717c7

Add random read capability to http store

Allow client accesses partial image content from glance store.

Change-Id: I7b8e12610d57f262e9edd2bd997f2df61d734339
Co-authored-by: Sabari Kumar Murugesan <smurugesan@vmware.com>
Signed-off-by: Zhi Yan Liu <zhiyanl@cn.ibm.com>

[{'created': '2014-11-28 20:59:04.000000000', 'message': "Delegate string formatting to logger

This patch refactors some of the logging to delay performing string
formatting, which means that the formatting can be skipped if the log
level is set such that the message will not be emitted. This is already
done in some places, but this patch standardizes the where the
formatting is done.

The change is mostly along the lines of changing:

    LOG.debug('something is %s' % something)

into:

    LOG.debug('something is %s', something)

Change-Id: Iff7b76baa78675562dfbe8f2905806557cee245e
"}]
commit_message:
Delegate string formatting to logger

This patch refactors some of the logging to delay performing string
formatting, which means that the formatting can be skipped if the log
level is set such that the message will not be emitted. This is already
done in some places, but this patch standardizes the where the
formatting is done.

The change is mostly along the lines of changing:

    LOG.debug('something is %s' % something)

into:

    LOG.debug('something is %s', something)

Change-Id: Iff7b76baa78675562dfbe8f2905806557cee245e

commit_message:
Fixes issue when packaged with pyinstaller

The glanceclient module fails to load with a
"pkg_resources.DistributionNotFound" exception when
python-glanceclient is used by an application packaged
with pyinstaller.

Change-Id: Iab1baf214fafca7f8d68d15ded80a56f442b22cb
Closes-Bug: #1397557

commit_message:
Add the trigger field to the tasks table

This change adds the trigger field to the Tasks table as stated in the
spec. This field will be used to identify tasks that were triggered
automatically by a TaskTrigger.

This patch is the last one involving database changes related to this
bp.

Partially-Implements blueprint: task-engine-enhancement

Change-Id: Ia72fdec5720c86e4098c1d772f4c082944e685ff

[{'account_id': 11356, 'date': '2015-01-08 19:09:11.000000000', 'content': 'Uploaded patch set 1.'}, {'account_id': 11356, 'date': '2015-01-08 19:13:45.000000000', 'content': 'Uploaded patch set 2.'}, {'account_id': 11356, 'date': '2015-01-08 19:15:54.000000000', 'content': 'Patch Set 3: Commit message was updated'}, {'account_id': 2537, 'date': '2015-01-08 19:21:15.000000000', 'content': 'Patch Set 3: Code-Review-1

python-swiftclient retries 5 times by itself. What cases does this change handle?'}, {'account_id': 8158, 'date': '2015-01-08 19:40:03.000000000', 'content': "Patch Set 3:

Agree with Nikhil. 
Before we see a swiftclient.ClientExpection, on which a new retry is trigged from swift driver, swiftclient would have already tried five times. This really means we'll retry the get operation 25 times by default. Also, I'm not sure if this should be default.

Anyway, would like to hear Louis' use case here."}, {'account_id': 11356, 'date': '2015-01-08 19:45:20.000000000', 'content': 'Patch Set 3:

This retry continues with an offset based on how much image data is already downloaded. For example, if the image is 75% downloaded and the connection is broken, this retry will start a new request for the remaining 25% rather than throw away the data and start afresh.'}, {'account_id': 11356, 'date': '2015-01-08 19:45:56.000000000', 'content': 'Patch Set 3:

commit_message:
Default number of swift download retries to 5

This is a useful option to have enabled by default, giving resilience to
network outages during image downloads from swift. Other stores with retry
options (VMWare and cinder stores) also have them enabled by default.

DocImpact

Related-to: blueprint swift-retry-wait

Change-Id: Ia09b4ed5bd1fff73145df87fd1bced849a96b3da

commit_message:
Metadef namespace field namespace is not unique in MySQL

The metadef namespace model has a field called namespace which should be
unique across the database. It's used by the API to show details of the
namespace instead of the id (which is not exposed anywhere). In our
current implementation user is able to create two same namespaces, and
after that if he wish to list all the namespaces the 500 response will
be returned. Same response is returned when trying to get details of
this newly created namespace.

To reproduce this issue locally you need to:
1. Set the GLANCE_TEST_SQL_CONNECTION environment variable to point to
MySQL database connection, eg.
GLANCE_TEST_SQL_CONNECTION='mysql://root:pass@127.0.0.1/glance_test?charset=utf8'
2. Run specific test provided in this patch
tox -e py27 glance.tests.functional.v2.test_metadef_namespaces

Change-Id: I945e0c84b5e6a66c945c60ba0c8126d9111c0812
Closes-Bug: 1463036

commit_message:
Removed schema caching

Removed the schema caching function and unit tests
since the cache was not being used anywhere.
The schema caching function was used to determine
the glance api version.
It is replaced by the "__get_glance_api_version" function.

Closes-Bug: #1490635

Change-Id: Id4b7638357f379f17c48394990a378a6cdf0e240

commit_message:
Remove raising HTTP Errors

The Glanceclient currently raises HTTP errors, this is confusing as
it would make someone believe that something happened on the severside
to deny a request. These exceptions could have been raised without the
sever ever returning an error code.

Change-Id: Idd6bc7f5dd85176013997b52053d52052371e453
Closes-bug: 1493859

commit_message:
Move RBD calls to a separate threads

RBD is a python binding for librados which isn't patched by eventlet.

Making long-running tasks like creating big images blocks eventlet
loop and glance-api service hangs until it finished when
rados_connect_timeout is disabled. It makes glance-api services
unavailable for a while.

This patch moves all rados calls to a separate python thread which
doesn't block eventlet loop.

Change-Id: Ia39c334fba778045efd89e198eee00a32d15d134

commit_message:
add show_multiple_locations to sample glance-api.conf

The show_multiple_locations configuration option should be
included in the sample glance-api.conf that is shipped with
glance packages. Otherwise it is not clear in which config
section this option belongs.

Change-Id: Iced4a602a96fecd9484582ddb4a7816a72d027ed
Closes-Bug: #1486373

subject: Kilo backport
revisions:
[{'created': '2015-11-23 10:41:41.000000000', 'message': 'Kilo backport

Service_provider in neutron.conf
	In kilo it is not possible to add service
	provider config. Thats why the configuration has
	to be set in neutron.conf

Add namespace to extension
	In kilo an extension for neutron still
	needs a get_namespace method.

Hack around neutrons fixed plugin rules
	The list of allowed services is fixed in kilo.
	This commit adds BGPVPN to the allowed services.

Align unittests to kilo
	bgpvpn_id is given in kwargs not in args.

Change-Id: I0627dbf2c7887ef75d7e71883d7f010f741bf978
'}]
commit_message:
Kilo backport

Service_provider in neutron.conf
	In kilo it is not possible to add service
	provider config. Thats why the configuration has
	to be set in neutron.conf

Add namespace to extension
	In kilo an extension for neutron still
	needs a get_namespace method.

Hack around neutrons fixed plugin rules
	The list of allowed services is fixed in kilo.
	This commit adds BGPVPN to the allowed services.

Align unittests to kilo
	bgpvpn_id is given in kwargs not in args.

Change-Id: I0627dbf2c7887ef75d7e71883d7f010f741bf978

Kilo backport

Service_provider in neutron.conf
	In kilo it is not possible to add service
	provider config. Thats why the configuration has
	to be set in neutron.conf

Add namespace to extension
	In kilo an extension for neutron still
	needs a get_namespace method.

Hack around neutrons fixed plugin rules
	The list of allowed services is fixed in kilo.
	This commit adds BGPVPN to the allowed services.

Align unittests to kilo
	bgpvpn_id is given in kwargs not in args.

Change-Id: I7ea7b78c63d4e2c7ed47862f9febe9e3cd3b9a57

commit_message:
Don't set environment variables in tox.ini

Because of the bug [1] in tox 2.2.1 tox there's a need
to hard-code all environment variables except
the ones which are not set by Fuel CI.

This patch will be reverted as soon as [1] is fixed.

1. https://bitbucket.org/hpk42/tox/issues/285/tox-220-breaks-some-toxini-config-files

Closes-bug: #1517427
Change-Id: I32903c1fd5545ca56410789add7d9c2a8bbacba7

commit_message:
L3 agent: skip routers notifications if fullsync is true

In case l3 agent is about to fullsync there is no point in processing
routers_updated notifications separately.
This should decrease the (unneeded) load on neutron server at high
scale.

Closes-Bug: #1509295
Change-Id: Ic20b767f34903e9bf14f4616632af3b8698dcebb

commit_message:
Kilo backport

Service_provider in neutron.conf
	In kilo it is not possible to add service
	provider config. Thats why the configuration has
	to be set in neutron.conf

Add namespace to extension
	In kilo an extension for neutron still
	needs a get_namespace method.

Hack around neutrons fixed plugin rules
	The list of allowed services is fixed in kilo.
	This commit adds BGPVPN to the allowed services.

Align requirements to kilo

Deliver bgpvpn_id through network_association dict
	In kilo the parent_id can not be transported
	thats way the bgpvpn_id is included in the
	network_association.

	in neutronclient/v2_0/client.py:
    def extend_create(self, resource_singular, path):
            def _fx(body=None):
	                return self.create_ext(path, body)
			        setattr(self, "create_%s" %
				resource_singular, _fx)

Align unittests to kilo
	bgpvpn_id is given in kwargs not in args.

Change-Id: Ie2043c5d6fe70a53e295c12aba724db49ad157db

(3 comments)'}, {'account_id': 10391, 'date': '2015-10-30 10:49:09.000000000', 'content': "Patch Set 3: Code-Review-2

It's generally a bad idea to disallow plugin enablement if serialization is failed. It may fail because one of network roles requests 5 VIPs in public network (by default), but that doesn't mean this network role will be assigned on public. You can move it to another network (thanks to network templating, and advanced networking one day).

It should be fix on other way - the network serializer MUST NOT allocate any stuff, or try to resolve network roles conflicts and so on. It should simply return things as they are.

In this particular case, the network_configuration API handler shouldn't try to allocate VIPs. It should return *already* allocated VIPs and no more.

Please, see ML [1]

[1] http://lists.openstack.org/pipermail/openstack-dev/2015-October/077421.html"}, {'account_id': 9377, 'date': '2015-10-30 13:13:09.000000000', 'content': "Patch Set 3:

@Aleksey Thx for helpful comments.

@Igor I'm fully understand that is *not* the best idea. 

But still, you can not be disagree that activating plugin should not break serialization of net config regardless of how it works. So, in perfect way this change will become useless but not destructive. And it is definitely useful for now. 
So my suggestion is: let's add suggested check, put your idea (which is sounds really reasonable for me) in #TODO and file another bug for fix the net config serialization.
Thoughts?"}, {'account_id': 9377, 'date': '2015-10-30 17:20:02.000000000', 'content': 'Uploaded patch set 4.'}, {'account_id': 3, 'date': '2015-10-30 17:31:53.000000000', 'content': 'Patch Set 4: Verified-1

commit_message:
telemetry client: accept 307 for create_alarm request

Ceilometer API redirects Alarming requests to Aodh API service.
The return code is not 201 but 307 which is temporary in Liberty cycle
until Ceilometer Alarm is really replaced by Aodh everywhere.

Change-Id: Ide9f6360a6e7468be51003c5a8b051874377c645
Closes-bug: #1509885

commit_message:
Remove vip for rabbitmq

Adjust all the configs to list all the rabbitmq hosts rather than
running rabbitmq through the VIP. This is made possible by clusterer
which has already merged.

Change-Id: I5db48f5f10ec68f4c8863a29bc13984f6845a4f9
Partially-Implements: blueprint rabbitmq-clusterer
(cherry picked from commit 347730cec83796c584162b235f5f18786b20f6ed)

commit_message:
Fix config loading when running the watcher-api

This regression was caused when we upgrade the version of olso.
Unfortunately this issue wasn't picked up with the unit tests as
the cmds doesn't have unit tests yet.

Error message: "watcher-api fail with NoSuchOptError: no such option:debug"

This patchset implements unit tests for:

- 'watcher-api' command
- 'watcher-db-manage' command (and sub-command)
- 'watcher-applier' command

Change-Id: I2bea8aee28dec913ebc45f2824bf474f86652642

I could go either way.  Pep8 required flake8, which is for linting python. ansible-lint, is specific to ansible, and also include ansible-playbook --syntax-check.

Personally, I see if the same as puppet, where they actually have separate -lint and -syntax checks (we have compressed into -lint).'}, {'account_id': 6816, 'date': '2015-11-19 12:56:13.000000000', 'content': "Patch Set 3:

Yeah, if the intent is to have a consolidated job for linting then perhaps the 'pep8' jobs should all be renamed to a general 'lint' job instead and all projects should be asked to merge the separated lint jobs into one. commit_message:
Create ansible-role-jobs for JJB and zuul

In an effort to reduce duplicate code, we've created an
ansible-role-jobs templaste.  Any new ansible module should use this
template.

We still have a few projects not using this, but will be converted
once their local tox.ini files have been updated.

Change-Id: I20012637ee0fa04ff910c13630b3b3aa5ce230eb
Depends-On: I1815c42f74df237e810332b55c0e890d80ebada9
Depends-On: I83ae3bb426c1a951216e2ca0509d1b5ab5020ecc
Signed-off-by: Paul Belanger <pabelanger@redhat.com>

revisions:
[{'created': '2015-11-20 16:46:24.000000000', 'message': 'Update exception import path

Newer versions of ironicclient have removed the openstack.common
package and moved the apiclient code into simply
ironicclient.common.  This change maintains compatibility with
both versions of ironicclient by trying both imports.

Change-Id: I8b7523f08b39b4f88a64bca6bcf800619e14fcad
'}, {'created': '2015-11-20 18:16:34.000000000', 'message': "Don't import ironicclient exceptions from openstack.common

Importing from another projects openstack.common is not good, and
now that ironicclient has moved openstack.common to
ironicclient.common it has broken us.  Use ironicclient.exc
instead.

Change-Id: I8b7523f08b39b4f88a64bca6bcf800619e14fcad
"}]
commit_message:
Don't import ironicclient exceptions from openstack.common

Importing from another projects openstack.common is not good, and
now that ironicclient has moved openstack.common to
ironicclient.common it has broken us.  Use ironicclient.exc
instead.

Change-Id: I8b7523f08b39b4f88a64bca6bcf800619e14fcad

commit_message:
Add missing packages to dev-quickstart

Pillow now requires to have libjpeg installed, this change adds it
to the list of binary dependencies for unit tests in developer
quickstart guide.

Closes-bug: #1516782

commit_message:
get_running_processes: don't list 'kernel' as a pid

fuser shows some of kernel accesses (mount points, swap files, etc)
using the string 'kernel' as a pid. Ignore such a pseudo-pid to
avoid the spurious errors and noise in the logs.

This CR effectively re-applies #245654 [0] which was merged 
five days ago, but was accidentally reverted by #246575 [1] 
due to some unknown issues during merge to master.
This could easily be seen from commit to master on GitHub [2]
[0] - https://review.openstack.org/#/c/245654
[1] - https://review.openstack.org/#/c/246575
[2] - https://github.com/openstack/fuel-agent/commit/c33563d56172f605e2a2819d11504513f583b51c

Change-Id: Ia0cb7ef41812d854b53e52fbb4e06fd86622fb87

Drop root for gnocchi

Updates to ensure commands run in the gnocchi containers
are done as the 'gnocchi' user rather than root.

@Kairat It does make it slightly easier to review, however IMO with small changes on lots of files its relatively easy to review each file anyway.

Without the files squashed the two changes could end up being pushed in at separate times, meaning that half the code base still uses the 'old version' and the other half uses the 'new version'.

Therefore, I think the case for squashing the changes would be a better approach and agree with Flavio."}, {'account_id': 14676, 'date': '2015-11-23 08:48:59.000000000', 'content': 'Abandoned

Squashed into previous commit'}]

commit_message:
Import i18n functions for all modules directly

Finish importing of i18n functions from module directly.
It allows to make code shorter and prevent the situation when
translation function is not needed anymore but present in module
global variables(that happens because pep8 doesn't check usage of
module vars).
Also deleted some unused i18 imports from modules.

Change-Id: Ib089b2cbadcaa817ea30de59b6091b1d6d2259a1

commit_message:
Cleanup support-compute.rst usage

The file is only used by admin-guide-cloud, so move it from common to
that directory.
Remove all exclude_patterns that mention support-compute.rst.
Remove XML version of the file since it's unused.

Change-Id: Ia1e72ed42a48aeaa3c35072330a33bdbe3e42573

commit_message:
Fix cron-trigger's execution with pattern and first time

When creating cron-trigger with the following command:
mistral cron-trigger-create cron1 simple_wf --pattern '*/1 * * * *'
--first-time '2015-11-12 13:28'

The cron-trigger should be executed for every 1 minute over and over
again.

Change-Id: Id6a8c9a747bb56c8bea302cdd86d1e64b99f4eab
Closes-Bug: #1515488

commit_message:
Drop now unused PERC variables

Two functions defined in common_translation_update set $PERC variables,
which are no longer referenced since Transifex support was dropped,
remove them.

Change-Id: I32044abffca0321d31f21f63b2f97d5e78fe8dce

commit_message:
Initial commit

Add structure, unit tests, and template for mistral-specs, creating
a functional specs repository without any approved specs.

Put example.rst in mitaka/approved and mitaka/implemented respectively
to avoid doc build warnings:
"pattern u'specs/mitaka/approved/*' didn't match any documents"

Implements: blueprint mistral-spec-repository
Change-Id: I092ec2f9b1aef9b1bf328658674119eb3cdf3380

I am ok with adding vhost support, but I think it's fair to raise the profile of this 'feature'. This ain't a bug fix"}, {'account_id': 13869, 'date': '2015-10-30 16:49:32.000000000', 'content': "Patch Set 13:

There is not only one mechanism driver (i.e. ovs-dpdk) using vhostuser vif-type to accelerate open-vswitch.

In networking-6wind, we have a mechanism driver ovs-fp [1] also using vhostuser for openvswich. It's based on the fast path technology.  It is an user-space stack for high performance packets offloading Linux networking functions: ip routing, linux bridge, OVS, iptables, conntrack...

We could potentially due similar changes (but different) in the mechanism driver/agent openvswitch in the neutron tree instead of forking theses ones in networking-6wind.

I am wondering, if we could have a more modular approach to support ovs-dpdk and ovs-fp by having extension to add different vif-type in the ML2 ovs mechanism driver and also for the ovs agent.

In fact, something similar to what it have been for qos support in openvswitch but for vif-type like vhost-user.

[1] https://github.com/openstack/networking-6wind/blob/master/networking_6wind/ml2_drivers/mech_ovs_fp.py"}, {'account_id': 748, 'date': '2015-10-30 21:37:51.000000000', 'content': "Patch Set 13:

We had a discussion at the summit on how to provide better extensibility in the ovs agent [1]. The reason why I didn't bring it up in the context of this review is that this patch looks rather trivial to handle, and I wouldn't want to open up the possibility of an 'app store' for vhost drivers just yet. Choice is good, but too many choices without providing a way of discerning how solutions compare and contrast to one another is not beneficial for the user, and therefore I wouldn't want to promote it.

By looking at your pointer, I can see how we could reconcile easily the driver side, but there is very little information supplied to understand how the agent side is affected. Perhaps you can elaborate a little? That said, it feels premature going down the path of extensibility for vhost right now: documentation, usability and testing should come first, whereas crowding this space should come second.

[1] https://etherpad.openstack.org/p/mitaka-neutron-core-extensibility"}, {'account_id': 11604, 'date': '2015-10-30 22:01:05.000000000', 'content': 'Patch Set 13:

this patchset removes the need for the ovsdpdk ml2 mech driver provided by networking-ovs-dpdk repo. the networking-ovs-dpdk repo also provides an openflow based ovs security group driver and a devstack plugin to build,install and configure standard ovs compiled with dpdk.

the networking-ovs-dpdk will continue to exist and be developed to implement new functionality but will nolonger be required to enable vhost-user support with standard ovs + dpdk .'}, {'account_id': 11604, 'date': '2015-10-31 00:43:34.000000000', 'content': 'Patch Set 13:

ill pull the conversation i had with terry from the rfe bug  into a spec on etherpad (https://etherpad.openstack.org/p/ovs-vhost-user-support-via-capabilities-detection) and then submit to gerrit for reivew next week.

i have an hour and a half before my flight boards so ill see what i can get done and pick it back up on tuesday.

ill limit the scope of the spec to just the enablement of vhost-user with standard ovs from openvswich.org( http://github.com/openvswitch/ovs) with the ovs dpdkvhostuser port type.

the agent type disscustion can evolve separately via the RFE bug opened by maxime(https://etherpad.openstack.org/p/ovs-vhost-user-support-via-capabilities-detection)

@armando
are you interested in/ have bandwidth to oversee the bluepirnt/spec or should i reach out to some of the other core developers to take that role. im not sure how the spec/blurepint changes effect that so ill just pull together a spec and submit it for review and we can go from there.'}, {'account_id': 11604, 'date': '2015-10-31 01:25:41.000000000', 'content': 'Patch Set 13:

(1 comment)'}, {'account_id': 11604, 'date': '2015-10-31 02:19:05.000000000', 'content': 'Uploaded patch set 14.'}, {'account_id': 13869, 'date': '2015-10-31 02:23:48.000000000', 'content': "Patch Set 14:

> Armando

First point about 'vhostuser app-store':

We have already many different solutions for l2 switch in the neutron tree. Why it should be different regarding vhostuser ?

In fact, user is already aware that are different solutions to accelerate switch performance based on vhostuser, like snabb switch, fast path, ovs dpdk, opencontrail dpdk.

I am here to better integrate your solution in the openstack ecosystem. It's why we create networking-6wind repository and we add recently a CI: https://wiki.openstack.org/wiki/ThirdPartySystems/6WIND_Networking_CI.

Second point about 'agent side':

The agent needs to detect capacity on the node and report this one to the mechanism driver:
- for ovs-dpdk: detect/report datapath_type and interface supported
- for ovs-fp: detect/report if the fast path process is running

Basically, we will add the capacity to add some extra informations in the configuration field of the agent_state."}, {'account_id': 3, 'date': '2015-10-31 03:44:40.000000000', 'content': 'Patch Set 14: Verified+1

revisions:
[{'created': '2015-10-19 22:21:16.000000000', 'message': "Add vhost-user support via ovs capabilities/datapath_type

Adds the ovs 'config' property which returns the contents of the
single row of the Open_vSwitch table. This gives access to certain
OVS capabilities such as datapath_types and iface_types.

Using this information in concert with the datapath_type config

commit_message:
Add vhost-user support via ovs capabilities/datapath_type

Adds the ovs 'config' property which returns the contents of the
single row of the Open_vSwitch table. This gives access to certain
OVS capabilities such as datapath_types and iface_types.

Using this information in concert with the datapath_type config
option, vif details are calculated by the OVS mech driver. If
datapath_type == 'netdev' and OVS on the agent host is capable of
supporting dpdkvhostuser, then it is used.

Authored-By: Terry Wilson <twilson@redhat.com>
Co-Authored-By: Sean Mooney <sean.k.mooney@intel.com>

Closes-Bug: #1506127
Change-Id: I5047f1d1276e2f52ff02a0cba136e222779d059c

commit_message:
VPN forms help text could be improved

The help text (both tooltips, and descriptive text on the right hand side) for VPN forms (Create, Edit etc.) is very sparse, and we should update it with more information from the VPN docs or API docs.

Fix bug1516603

Change-Id: Ica0efa4aca107ea353213a43159be40865ee549e

commit_message:
Use setup_develop instead of setup_package in plugin.sh

Since all mistral requirements are match with global requirements
it is more correct to use setup_develop function.
Info about this function and difference with setup_package
function can be found here:
https://github.com/openstack-dev/devstack/blob/master/inc/python

Change-Id: I8b283df8734675f92d9bc8266bafe7cece6fb5f9

commit_message:
Reduce vdu2 flavor from  ml.medium to ml.tiny

Some dsvm nodes may has little memory which cannot provide enough
for multiple VDU tests. This patch reduces the vdu2's flavor into
ml.tiny.

Change-Id: Ia7ddc7656d4909e0e977915f70a97baedb782ed9
Closes-bug: 1516204
(cherry picked from commit 3fff7accf2256bcc24d6393c5edecb7bfb0503a3)

commit_message:
Update http_image path to a cirros image file

Current path is for gz file and i changed it to img.
The glance image path is going to be used in new testcases
glance v2 image import supports in import image for http.
We need to set a real image path and not gz.

I run tox -egenconfig
Change-Id: I01703a0e222fbda1ae3ec525936325340fca21ff

commit_message:
Ignore Content-Type from client on multipart-manifest=delete

Otherwise, if a client includes something like:

    Content-Type: application/x-www-form-urlencoded

...we won't delete anything, and instead send back:

    Number Deleted: 0
    Number Not Found: 0
    Response Body:
    Response Status: 406 Not Acceptable
    Errors:

...despite the fact that we're managing the iterator, so we know it's
acceptable.

Change-Id: I791c7bda1d9df830d8dacd3783c2393db5a9ac09

commit_message:
Fix error when listing stacks

Previously the stack list command would error out if any stacks were
present. This was due to the action code attempting to index on a
stack object, rather than grabbing its attributes. This change switches
the action code to use the proper utility for a resource instead of
a dict.

Change-Id: Ia6b73d5c1ba7f7e3d7bc5493167da81062102b42
Blueprint: heat-support-python-openstackclient

commit_message:
Unify the image-list output of v1 and v1 for verbose and nonverbose

Output of the “glance image-list” is different in glance API v1 and v2 with
option verbose and nonverbose.

Current image-list output is;
v1 verbose/nonverbose
 ['ID', 'Name', 'Disk Format', 'Container Format',  'Size', 'Status']
v2 nonverbose
['ID', 'Name']
v2 verbose
['ID', 'Name', 'Disk_format', 'Container_format', 'Size', 'Status','Owner']

Should unify the image-list output of v1 and v2 for verbose and non-verbose.
v1/v2 nonverbose
['ID', 'Name']
v1/v2 verbose
['ID', 'Name', 'Disk_format', 'Container_format', 'Size', 'Status','Owner']

Change-Id: Ic40d08b4d9058d5c3a97e1f092c4825c5b40d8cb
Closes-Bug: #1489543

commit_message:
Ignore KeyError for secret field

Although it doesn't make sense to create a datasource without
providing auth info in config info, it may be not possible to
define a schema to verify because different datasource drivers
may use different kinds of auth methods. So we should be able
to handle the case that none secret info is provided. The fix
just simply ignores KeyError exception here.

Change-Id: I06bc6a4fb659d862da96dd96557454b6385d003f
Closes-Bug: #1492354

[{'created': '2015-11-10 23:53:31.000000000', 'message': 'Map keystoneclient exceptions to keystoneauth

To allow people to use a keystoneauth session with keystoneclient we
need to make it so that any exceptions that keystoneclient catch are the
same as what keystoneauth might throw.

The only practical way to do this is to map the keystoneclient
exceptions onto the keystoneauth equivalents. This is fairly easy as all
these exceptions were extracted from keystoneclient initially.

commit_message:
Map keystoneclient exceptions to keystoneauth

To allow people to use a keystoneauth session with keystoneclient we
need to make it so that any exceptions that keystoneclient catch are the
same as what keystoneauth might throw.

The only practical way to do this is to map the keystoneclient
exceptions onto the keystoneauth equivalents. This is fairly easy as all
these exceptions were extracted from keystoneclient initially.

Closes-Bug: #1515048
Change-Id: I3b74b0ba1e1f9dda937a2d90e2d75ff0b7597a9b

commit_message:
handle connection from multiple ovsdb servers

ovsdb server initiates the connection to l2gw agent with the entries in
manager table in ovsdb hardware vtep schema and with flag 'enable_manager'
set to True in l2gateway_agent.ini.
multiple ovsdb can connect to same l2gatway agent with the l2gw agent ip in
respective manager table.
This patchset addresses the handling of connections from multiple
ovsdb servers.

Change-Id: Iffe6a9e8599ffaed55c3f8b749c4d6f7d0e52c79
Closes-Bug:1495005

commit_message:
[networking] Add unused common/* to exclude_patterns

In the networking guide, only app_support, conventions and
glossary are referred to and all other files are unused.
To avoid unnecessary warnings during build, unused common files
should be added to excluded_patterns in conf.py.

Change-Id: Ide56ad3f39fd152576e3681101822f5644a5cbbd

commit_message:
[networking] Use explicit reference for section link

In sphinx, we can use a reference by a title name, but it does
not work when a title is translated. Instead we should use
an explicit reference for section link.
It is required to avoid an error of translation build.

Change-Id: I0ec8109088946ec5bc0b63d2e09ec021f3b5307c

commit_message:
Updating rally.conf.sample

If you clone rally and execute `tox -e genconfig`, you will see
that rally.conf.sample has some changes. It is because new release
of the oslo.log library has recently happened. Also rally.conf.sample
has some changes related to Sahara. So it looks like someone forgot to
execute `tox -e genconfig` before submitting the changes.

Change-Id: I582d3005d30705d34060e649d224808c419a2c69

commit_message:
Adds Swift Versioning Support

This patch overrides the allowed_versions value in the
/etc/swift/container-server.conf file to true.  This matches
the original behavior in the swift-storage image element and
is needed for tripleo-common[1].

[1] http://bit.ly/1j3JlK4

Change-Id: I6f97463fc6572dd507624223071931cd8c0a4653

commit_message:
Fix for HP 3rd Party CI failure

This patchset fixes the problem in HP L2GW CI where timeout
errors were reported.
Patchset also ensures that all the tests run in sequential order.

Change-Id: I977b52ba87112b3d5b7aefee408bd3d14c632fec
Closes-bug: 1517758

commit_message:
[admin-guide-cloud] Fix missing label

Use :doc: instead of :ref: for reference to document
to fix these kind of warnings:

  SphinxWarning: openstack-manuals/doc/admin-guide-cloud/source/keystone_tokens.rst:21:
  WARNING: undefined label: keystone_fernet_token_faq (if the link has no
  caption the label must precede a section header)

And similar for keystone_certificates_for_pki.

Fix capitalization of Fernet in title.

Change-Id: I330cccfbd363f46f77bffb305be010ab9aaf0db0

commit_message:
neutron-db-manage: expose alembic 'heads' command

This command shows current heads in all alembic branches. Even without
the command, we *can* get the heads values by looking into *_HEAD files
in tree. Still, those files may be missing; and the command is a tiny
bit more easy to use. Also, it gives access to more details on head
revisions if used with --verbose.

(2 comments)

I think we can invite people to review this in its current form as a way of getting cross-project input. (ie, perhaps broadcast this more widely before it's merged etc).

This looks good from my point of view (and with my infra hat on). I don't see any reason why we couldn't do what is listed. Most of the change is social and in my opinion that's more up to the documentation and project teams who are affected by it.

The largest technical challenge that I can see is that a string after "DocImpact" may not be enough and how do we format a commit message in an appropriate way. This is the reason for my -1. I'd like to see some more thoughts about the level of detail required in the new docimpact syntax.

If we're going to end up with huge documentation explanations in commit messages, are we better off putting them elsewhere. Perhaps with a file in tree. Or even a file in another docs repo (that the docimpact can point to the change-id of, or have a cross-repo depends-on etc).'}, {'account_id': 9162, 'date': '2015-11-12 00:37:16.000000000', 'content': "Patch Set 5:

new, improved examples.

commit_message:
Add os-win to requirements.txt

A common library abstracting Windows specific operations has been
created in order to remove duplicated code among OpenStack projects,
also being easier to maintain.

This patch adds os-win to global requirements so that the Windows
drivers may use it.

Change-Id: I796f8849dec1c46b99595c096b1c4b10b5a0221f
Partially-implements: blueprint windows-os-win

commit_message:
Fix client UnauthorizedError

Zaqar server threw UnauthorizedError when client
try to execute any cli command.

This patch fixes the issue and changes the default
authorization backend from noauth to keystone.

Change-Id: I88c2f5aa914b5fb40b6dc16a256d3e385d9aaa23
Closes-Bug: #1491738

commit_message:
Add 300 as a normal response code for Identity's "List versions"

Apparently, either "200 OK" or "300 Multiple Options" may be considered
normal depending on the client's Accept header [1], though in the
not-too-distant past 300 was the *only* normal response code [2].

[1] https://github.com/openstack/keystone/blob/2015.1.2/keystone/controllers.py#L168-L182
[2] https://github.com/openstack/keystone/blob/2014.1/keystone/controllers.py#L137-L143

Change-Id: I1b3b13abef0638ed832c0b3ba2682e6cbadacae7

Fix a type of parameter "xsd:list"

The following parameters should be fixed "xsd:list".

* "Subnet" parameters
  "allocation_pools"
  "dns_nameservers"

* Port parameters
  "allowed_address_pairs"
  "extra_dhcp_opts"
  "fixed_ips"
  "security_groups"

* SubnetPool parameters
  "prefixes"

* Securit-Group-Rule
  "security_group_rules"

* Service Providers
  "service_providers"

* Router parameters
  "external_fixed_ips"

* Network parameters
  "subnets"
  "segments"

Closes-Bug: #1512660

commit_message:
Reverse order of values in for compute boot_index

The current docs for the boot_index parameter to block_device_mapping_v2
are backwards, suggesting that -1 be given for boot volume and 0 for
other volumes. The opposite is true according to both the novaclient
shell code and doc/source/block_device_mapping.rst in the nova source
tree. The new paragraph is taken directly from that nova source
document.

Change-Id: Id050903a8c71cac6324007429dfd30f40da10c48

commit_message:
do_build_image: move image creation to a helper method

Move the code which actually makes compressed filesystem images
of the installed/configured OS from do_build_image into a helper
method. The next patch will implement the make_bootstrap_image
method which packs the OS as a bootstrap image, that is, a tarball
containing a squashfs root filesystem, kernel, initramfs, and
a metadata.

Change-Id: I81d6697fa6ea75312eb9a836f714be789499178d
Implements: blueprint dynamically-build-bootstrap

commit_message:
Split generation of the docker repo file and it's installation

This resolves a possible case where piping directly to sudo
tee would hang and apparently wait for a keystroke.

Change-Id: Ic90cc6a61fa04e0367867789fb3d40c5305a636a
Closes-bug: #1518659

[{'created': '2015-11-03 12:13:23.000000000', 'message': "Update neutron_migrations_facts

This change does the following to neutron_migrations_facts:

- updates MIGRATIONS dict by adding entries for each neutron
  sub-project while also adding keys to track which sub-projects are
  installed and which migrations need to be run (contract or expand)
- takes subproject migrations into account (neutron-lbaas as an
  example)
- updates neutron_venv_lib_dir and neutron_non_venv_lib_dir by removing
  reference to neutron specifically since these vars need to be used
  for all neutron subprojects also

We also update neutron_db_setup.yml to use MIGRATIONS['run_contract']
and MIGRATIONS['run_expand'] to determine if neutron or a subproject
has migrations which need to be applied.

NOTE: I could not backport the change originally submitted to master as
      that change uses a new option added to neutron-db-manage in
      Mitaka that allows you to associate a revision with an alembic
      branch.  This option was not backported to liberty and therefore
      we have to resort to traversing the filesystem to match a
      revision to a branch.

Closes-Bug: #1511756

Change-Id: I3a385f4530620718ba01a7b5e993ba08ce38f7c7

commit_message:
Update neutron_migrations_facts

This change does the following to neutron_migrations_facts:

- updates MIGRATIONS dict by adding entries for each neutron
  sub-project while also adding keys to track which sub-projects are
  installed and which migrations need to be run (contract or expand)
- takes subproject migrations into account (neutron-lbaas as an
  example)
- updates neutron_venv_lib_dir and neutron_non_venv_lib_dir by removing
  reference to neutron specifically since these vars need to be used
  for all neutron subprojects also

We also update neutron_db_setup.yml to use MIGRATIONS['run_contract']
and MIGRATIONS['run_expand'] to determine if neutron or a subproject
has migrations which need to be applied.

This cherry-pick has a small edit to change 'mitaka' to 'liberty' in
playbooks/roles/os_neutron/tasks/neutron_db_setup.yml in order to
apply the series name appropriately.

Closes-Bug: #1511756
Change-Id: I3a385f4530620718ba01a7b5e993ba08ce38f7c7
(cherry picked from commit edd50471d9807d64504f7f04496f23bbbafbb221)

commit_message:
Keystone domain fix

The keystone module is not able to function when using Keystone
and the multi-domain backend. This issue is caused because the
domain argument is not passed into the client calls. to resolve
this issue the module has been updated to pass through the domain
to the various client calls where needed

Change-Id: I4882c1e164f8c6ceb6d19bc652b8a02d4c1a5224
Signed-off-by: Kevin Carter <kevin.carter@rackspace.com>

commit_message:
Avoiding usage of mutables as default arguments

Using Mutables objects as default arguments in function
definition is a known Python pitfall. This patch fixes
the issue in neutron-lbaas.

Change-Id: Idb1cccbebec5dfedde04ee474036e67569406caa
Closes-Bug: #1327473
(cherry picked from commit 0aac2d029a7ed9bff903a00a4ab194e277dfe06c)

The attribute named _local_network_vswitch was called as local_network_vswitch
in the agent resulting in an AttributeError.

This fix adds the propper naming, _local_network_vswitch.

Change-Id: If6ac53656b18d4698953e8357030d59723aad2dc
Closes-Bug: #1514313
(cherry picked from commit 9767ce67fbdc7b128601c8cfb96c5e8008a2c956)
'}]
commit_message:
Fixes bug: AttributeError when trying to use local_network_vswitch

The attribute named _local_network_vswitch was called as local_network_vswitch
in the agent resulting in an AttributeError.

This fix adds the propper naming, _local_network_vswitch.

Change-Id: If6ac53656b18d4698953e8357030d59723aad2dc
Closes-Bug: #1514313
(cherry picked from commit 9767ce67fbdc7b128601c8cfb96c5e8008a2c956)

commit_message:
remove precise from the supported list

We haven't been testing master on precise for a long time, and changes
are coming that won't work on precise. If people want to keep running
on precise they should realize they are on their own with it. And that
we won't block any changes that use it.

Change-Id: I3697f1c2409ad08f49793dabb37011606188e6f6

commit_message:
Update TODO work items

Claim the following work items:
- Complete unit test for engine/parser [1]
- Implement an abstraction for general reciever support [2]

Low Priority:
- Implement support for Monasca based alarm triggers [3]

I have added the appropriate bp's to account for these, and have added these to the etherpad [4].

[1]https://bugs.launchpad.net/senlin/+bug/1515229
[2]https://blueprints.launchpad.net/senlin/+spec/support-general-receiver-abstraction
[3]https://blueprints.launchpad.net/senlin/+spec/implement-monasca-alarm
[4]https://etherpad.openstack.org/p/senlin-mitaka-workitems

Change-Id: I845832200f1623e8c23177cf0fa824ef378024ab

commit_message:
Remove db access from XIV/DS8K CG functions

The XIV/DS8K driver no longer needs to access the db in order to
grab snapshots and volumes for the following functions:
* delete_consistencygroup
* create_cgsnapshot
* delete_cgsnapshot

Change-Id: I3762577c7c797e3f677cc4516b747990dfabfa4e

@Stuart, yes - this is description of SingleTenant driver and we have to mention it in the doc.

But I have one question about your phrase in the bug: "
The trick was to comment out the following lines:

# default_swift_reference = ref1
#swift_store_config_file = /etc/glance/glance-swift-store.conf
"

As far as I know now this is the only one way to configure Swift, in other case deprecated parameters will be used.

Does it mean that MultiTenant Driver doesn't support swift+config sheme?'}, {'account_id': 455, 'date': '2015-11-13 16:25:59.000000000', 'content': "Patch Set 4:

> Does it mean that MultiTenant Driver doesn't support swift+config sheme?

Correct.

swift+config was originally created so as to avoid having to store the password in the database. The multi-tenant store doesn't need to store a password so never used the swift+config scheme. Though support for that could potentially be added if we wanted to unify the config approach."}, {'account_id': 7745, 'date': '2015-11-16 14:39:05.000000000', 'content': 'Patch Set 4:

commit_message:
[docs] Update description of Glance-Swift conf options

This patch:

1. Updates the description of 4 deprecated options:
   * swift_store_auth_version
   * swift_store_auth_address
   * swift_store_user
   * swift_store_key
2. Adds a new sub-section: Configuring Swift configuration file.

Co-Authored-By: Mike Fedosin <mfedosin@mirantis.com>
Co-Authored-By: Olena Logvinova <ologvinova@mirantis.com>

Change-Id: I41baa2343cf92d819a4a64a2e269e1cb2e3be3f4
Closes-Bug: #1426813
Closes-Bug: #1509349

shade and by extension ansible have a default behavior of expanding
extra information on some resources. While that's great, some people
would prefer to not experience the cost of the extra API calls.

In support of those humans, introduce a flag, detailed_records, which

"}]
commit_message:
Add a flag to control default record expansion

shade and by extension ansible have a default behavior of expanding
extra information on some resources. While that's great, some people
would prefer to not experience the cost of the extra API calls.

In support of those humans, introduce a flag, detailed_records, which
defaults to True, to allow people to indicate they do not want such
a behavior.

Story: #2000413
Change-Id: I8ee9a271aa31c6e9b97eba2e71d5268d38f72759

commit_message:
Remove db access from 3PAR and LH cg functions

The HP 3PAR and HP LeftHand drivers no longer need to access the db in
order to grab snapshots and volumes for the following functions:
* delete_consistencygroup
* create_cgsnapshot
* delete_cgsnapshot

This patch removes all db access at the driver level for both 3PAR and
LeftHand drivers.

Change-Id: I2e29366573f53cf6e61939381bde5d04f188f42d

Cleanups to Vagrant documentation and scripts

The 'fields' argument wasn't being passed into the _get_collection
call so the results were always coming back with all of the fields.
This adds an API test to prevent a regression.

commit_message:
Fix use of fields argument in get_rbac_policies

The 'fields' argument wasn't being passed into the _get_collection
call so the results were always coming back with all of the fields.
This adds an API test to prevent a regression.

Change-Id: Iddef9dcc7639a557a9d19dc7265f10f98e002172
Closes-Bug: #1517815
(cherry picked from commit 09c032fa4e5177dea63e6139429309a11e62c65f)

commit_message:
Add IPv4Data and IPv6Data to the schema for the network

This patch adds the newly introduced properties, IPv4Data and IPv6Data,
in the request against /NetworkDriver.CreateNetwork. This patch covers
only the schema change to validate the request against
/NetworkDriver.CreateNetwork, and the actual logic to use the passed data
and create subnets is not implemented in this patch. It will be added in
the following patches.

Change-Id: I4e5cf7a0c8ea97c39e5450846818806408467352
Signed-off-by: Taku Fukushima <f.tac.mac@gmail.com>
Closes-Bug: #1514668

commit_message:
Additional VAG support for SolidFire

This patch removes volumes from volume access groups, and potentially volume
access groups, when a connection is terminated. When the previously added
'sf_enable_vag' option is enabled and a volume connection is terminated, if the
volume was part of a VAG then the volume is removed from the VAG. If the volume
is the only remaining volume in the VAG then the VAG is also removed.

Change-Id: Ib508a67f012f6f186abba0d381ab104edc163fa9
