Why doesn't glanceclient or glance_store or whatever library just handle the v1/v2(/v3?) stuff for glance automatically?  Why does this only live in nova - wouldn't heat or other clients also want this?"}, {'account_id': 6873, 'date': '2015-07-23 15:22:36.000000000', 'content': 'Patch Set 3:

(1 comment)'}, {'account_id': 11642, 'date': '2015-07-23 15:23:06.000000000', 'content': "Patch Set 3:

Oops. I updated the test and documentation sections. Thanks for the review and catching that Dane.

Testing will focus on the black box expected behavior of the system, verifying reliability and performance. Ultimately it doesn't matter if the downloads are concurrent, parallel, or serial. What matters is that we meet certain performance and reliability thresholds. Therefore, my focus will be on functional tests that verify the specified criteria.

Hope that helps, happy to discuss further. Thanks!"}, {'account_id': 15524, 'date': '2015-07-23 15:29:32.000000000', 'content': "Patch Set 3:

This is in nova-specs because it's not a TRUE seam, correct? In my view, there are still some minor changes that you'd have to make in Nova in order to 'abstract away' the differences between the various Glance APIs. For example v2 and up allows you to pass image metadata to Glance along with the snapshot itself, so Nova would have to change slightly to accommodate that functionality.

To be clear, I'm ok with this being in nova-specs. Generally speaking I'm very much in favor of anything that brings Nova up to date with the Glance API."}, {'account_id': 11642, 'date': '2015-07-23 16:06:22.000000000', 'content': 'Patch Set 3:

(1 comment)'}, {'account_id': 11642, 'date': '2015-07-23 16:13:51.000000000', 'content': "Patch Set 3:

Dane, I think we are on the same page.

It is correct that there will have to be refactoring in Nova to make this work. We have to untangle some things in Nova to cut the boundary. Trying to throw a library to Nova to use wouldn't work very well. It'd probably just get torn to shreds because it didn't meet the requirements of Nova. Making it happen in tree ensures it does what it ought to and allows for pulling out of tree later for sharing."}, {'account_id': 3, 'date': '2015-07-23 16:31:17.000000000', 'content': 'Patch Set 3: Verified+1

Build succeeded (check pipeline).

- gate-nova-specs-docs http://docs-draft.openstack.org/03/194303/3/check/gate-nova-specs-docs/b683f0e//doc/build/html/ : SUCCESS in 4m 20s

- gate-nova-specs-python27 http://logs.openstack.org/03/194303/3/check/gate-nova-specs-python27/3a67d24/ : SUCCESS in 2m 34s'}, {'account_id': 5441, 'date': '2015-07-23 17:56:21.000000000', 'content': 'Patch Set 3: Code-Review-1

(3 comments)'}, {'account_id': 11642, 'date': '2015-07-23 23:32:46.000000000', 'content': 'Patch Set 3:

(3 comments)'}, {'account_id': 7, 'date': '2015-07-25 20:21:20.000000000', 'content': 'Patch Set 3: Code-Review-1

(2 comments)

This spec is not well-scoped and it is not clear to me what precisely is being described as a "software seam" that doesn't already describe what we have in Nova already in nova/image/glance.py. What we have is horribly ugly, and the nova/image/download/ stuff is totally awful, but it *is* a software seam that allows Glance to work with Glance API servers publishing either v1 OR v2 APIs.

The performance and reliability stuff in this spec is not related to a software seam, IMHO.

Best,

-jay'}, {'account_id': 15524, 'date': '2015-07-27 00:02:23.000000000', 'content': 'Patch Set 3: Code-Review-1

I agree with the comments made about the use cases section. The discussion of performance/reliability does not seem totally relevant to the "software seam" part. Am I right to say that the use case is essentially that the end user, or a developer wants to leverage the functionality of Glance's v2/v3 API? The snapshot process in particular stands to benefit a lot from the functionality of v2+ (i.e. being able to pass image property metadata from Nova to Glance).

Perhaps for the sake of clarity and limited scope, it might be good to split this into two specs? The first could pertain more to the software seam in Nova and smoothing out the differences between Glance APIs, and the second could focus on the more complex reliability and performance improvements.'}, {'account_id': 11642, 'date': '2015-07-31 19:22:23.000000000', 'content': 'Patch Set 3:

I will update the spec to focus on an oslo-incubator style cleanup of the Glance code into a client library meant to be consumed by other projects (i.e. Nova, Cinder, etc.) and not users (i.e. no CLI, etc).

I will discuss python-glanceclient, Glance Store, and original proposal in the alternatives.

Based on concerns around scope, reliability and performance improvements can be made out of tree in the incubated library as a follow-up.

Thanks for the feedback!'}, {'account_id': 11642, 'date': '2015-07-31 20:30:15.000000000', 'content': 'Uploaded patch set 4.'}, {'account_id': 11642, 'date': '2015-07-31 20:31:47.000000000', 'content': "Patch Set 4:

I believe updates to spec should address all concerns raised so far. More feedback is appreciated and welcome.

Also, I'm looking for a Nova core to help support this and mentor the contributors (including myself).

Thanks!"}, {'account_id': 3, 'date': '2015-07-31 21:56:14.000000000', 'content': 'Patch Set 4: Verified+1

Build succeeded (check pipeline).

- gate-nova-specs-docs http://docs-draft.openstack.org/03/194303/4/check/gate-nova-specs-docs/3a951fe//doc/build/html/ : SUCCESS in 4m 38s

- gate-nova-specs-python27 http://logs.openstack.org/03/194303/4/check/gate-nova-specs-python27/7a890ab/ : SUCCESS in 2m 28s'}, {'account_id': 6159, 'date': '2015-08-02 02:46:58.000000000', 'content': "Patch Set 4: Code-Review-1

(4 comments)

As mentioned in the comments, I think what is being described here is exactly what glanceclient (or the SDK therefore) should be doing. Adding yet another layer on top of glanceclient won't solve the issue.

Also, if we really need this abstraction, I think we should have it in glanceclient anyway."}, {'account_id': 15524, 'date': '2015-08-03 13:58:35.000000000', 'content': 'Patch Set 4: Code-Review-1

(1 comment)

I find myself agreeing with Flavio that this spec is not doing enough to distinguish this "Glance seam" from what the glanceclient project is meant to provide. And I find myself agreeing that the complication of building and maintaining some additional layer between Nova/Cinder and Glance is difficult to justify as long as glanceclient exists and is also actively being built and maintained. 

I don't say this lightly, since I'd REALLY like to see some overhaul of Nova's interface with Glance to make it cleaner and up to date with improvements in Glance. Maybe the solution is, as Flavio seems to be suggesting, to improve glanceclient and enable Nova to use it?'}, {'account_id': 782, 'date': '2015-08-06 10:41:17.000000000', 'content': 'Patch Set 4: Code-Review-1

This looks like a good idea, in general, but...

Apologies this vote is late, but as announced on the ML we are not longer accepting specs for Liberty, as of June 25th 2015, and we have now completed the exception process for Liberty.
However, we are now open for Mitaka specs (with the hope to get most reviewed and merged before the summit). Please move this spec to the Mitaka directory.
For more details, please see: https://wiki.openstack.org/wiki/Nova/Liberty_Release_Schedule#Spec_and_Blueprint_Approval_Freeze
Any questions, please email me or find me on IRC johnthetubaguy'}, {'account_id': 782, 'date': '2015-08-06 10:44:28.000000000', 'content': 'Patch Set 4:

(2 comments)'}, {'account_id': 11642, 'date': '2015-08-07 15:10:42.000000000', 'content': 'Patch Set 4:

(6 comments)

I see the SDK / user interface as something separate from what the services consume though the potential for duplication is there.

The seam is basically a simpler library with a cleaner interface that would likely reuse much code in python-glanceclient. I believe there is value in putting python-glanceclient on a deprecation path and doing this in tree (i.e. oslo-incubator style or otherwise) to make sure we get it right and reduce the redundant leaky abstractions in the services (e.g. Nova and Cinder). We don't have to do that. We can update python-glanceclient in a vacuum and come back with a spec later to clean up Nova to use it. That path seems much slower and harder, and I predict abandoned work along that path (along with naming / limited scope problem python-glanceclient faces with the SDK work). This needs to be a collaboration effort to help mend the problems between these communities and these projects.

The real value here might be as simple as Nova and Glance people saying, up front, "Yes, this is a problem, let's work together and fix it." Rather than, "That's a Glance problem go away and come back with a solution, and we'll consider it then" / "Let's go create this wonderful thing in a vacuum and tell people to use it."'}, {'account_id': 15524, 'date': '2015-08-07 15:23:02.000000000', 'content': "Patch Set 4: -Code-Review

@Jesse: The workflow you've described in your comment sounds great to me. Will +1 as soon as a Mitaka spec is up."}, {'account_id': 11642, 'date': '2015-08-07 15:28:19.000000000', 'content': "Patch Set 4:

Thanks John. I'll update to mitaka folder after the discussion unfolds a bit more. I don't want to push up a change with all the comments on the current revision."}, {'account_id': 13997, 'date': '2015-09-05 14:51:11.000000000', 'content': 'Patch Set 4: Code-Review-1

(1 comment)'}, {'account_id': 15524, 'date': '2015-09-21 13:57:50.000000000', 'content': "Patch Set 4: Code-Review-1

What's the status of this spec? Are you still pursuing it for Mitaka?"}, {'account_id': 11642, 'date': '2015-09-22 01:29:34.000000000', 'content': "Patch Set 4:

Yes I am. However, I'm busy managing some internal work, and I won't be able to dig into this until October at the earliest, and probably November if I'm realistic. I'll try to clean up thins based on comments and git mv it on Thursday."}, {'account_id': 15524, 'date': '2015-09-23 14:28:13.000000000', 'content': 'Patch Set 4:

Understood. Thanks for the update.'}, {'account_id': 11642, 'date': '2015-09-28 14:11:55.000000000', 'content': "Patch Set 4:

Sorry, I was unable to get to this last week. I'll try again this week. If someone is interested in taking ownership of this and driving it, feel free. Otherwise, I will push forward as I have the cycles to do so."}, {'account_id': 4393, 'date': '2015-09-28 20:21:43.000000000', 'content': "Patch Set 4: Code-Review-1

I agree that this seems like a bad idea. If we have to build this extra thing, we've failed. If glanceclient needs some redirection, a new interface module, etc, then we should do that."}, {'account_id': 11642, 'date': '2015-09-28 20:31:58.000000000', 'content': 'Patch Set 4:

I agree with the we failed part.'}, {'account_id': 2750, 'date': '2015-11-20 14:37:53.000000000', 'content': 'Patch Set 4: Code-Review-1

The entire point of glanceclient existing is to provide such a stable interface.'}, {'account_id': 15524, 'date': '2015-11-20 14:40:34.000000000', 'content': 'Patch Set 4:

Does this https://review.openstack.org/#/c/231357/ preclude the need for this patch? I think it may be best to abandon the software seam approach.'}, {'account_id': 11642, 'date': '2015-11-20 14:46:57.000000000', 'content': "Abandoned

I'm now working on Ironic and don't have any time to dedicate to working on this problem. Also, Flavio has been leading an effort around v1 -> v2 changes that will hopefully resolve most of the pain."}]

commit_message:
Create a software seam for Glance API code in Nova

https://blueprints.launchpad.net/nova/+spec/glance-seam

Create a software seam that allows future upgrades to Glance API, as well as,
performance and reliability improvements for Glance requests (i.e. reliable
uploads and performant concurrent downloads) without major changes to Nova.
